# Fix Auction Flow and Sold Status Visibility

The user reports that the next player doesn't load automatically and the "Sold" status isn't clearly shown for the current player.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The auction will now automatically advance to the next player after a 5-second delay following a sale or unsold event. This ensures a continuous flow without requiring the host to manually click "Next" every time.

## Proposed Changes

### [Component Name] Backend Logic

#### [MODIFY] [server.js](file:///Users/shriyareddy/.gemini/antigravity/brain/3c732567-53c7-4226-be64-877b41286e7c/backend/server.js)
- Modify `processSoldPlayer` to:
    - Clear `room.activePlayer` (after emitting the event) to signal the end of the current bidding cycle.
    - Implement a `setTimeout` to automatically call `startNextAuction(roomId)` after 5 seconds.
- Ensure `startNextAuction` correctly resets all room-level bidding state (highestBid, leadingTeam, etc.).

---

### [Component Name] Frontend UI

#### [MODIFY] [AuctionRoom.jsx](file:///Users/shriyareddy/.gemini/antigravity/brain/3c732567-53c7-4226-be64-877b41286e7c/frontend/src/pages/AuctionRoom.jsx)
- Update the `auctionStateUpdate` listener to ensure it doesn't prematurely clear `soldEvent` if the `activePlayer` hasn't actually changed.
- Enhance the "Sold" overlay to ensure it's unmistakable.

## Open Questions
- Should the 5-second delay be configurable? (Currently hardcoded for simplicity).

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- N/A (Manual verification via browser tool).

### Manual Verification
1. Open the Auction Room.
2. Start the auction as Host.
3. Place a bid or let the timer run out.
4. Verify the "Sold/Unsold" overlay appears.
5. Verify the next player loads automatically after 5 seconds.
